WEBVTT

00:06.442 --> 00:07.466
What are they doing?

00:07.467 --> 00:09.701
Waitress gave them a
children's menu and crayons.

00:09.702 --> 00:12.704
They're trying to see who
can connect the dots first.

00:12.705 --> 00:13.939
Bear!

00:13.940 --> 00:15.640
Bear on a surfboard!

00:15.641 --> 00:17.476
I knew it. I sensed it.

00:17.477 --> 00:19.044
TEDDY: That's no fair.

00:19.045 --> 00:21.245
My crayon broke.

00:24.916 --> 00:26.618
I wasn't expecting
to see you here, Felix.

00:26.619 --> 00:28.453
I thought you were avoiding Langford's.

00:28.454 --> 00:30.455
Why? Because Emily works
here and she dumped me?

00:30.456 --> 00:31.623
Yes, the truth is, I have not

00:31.624 --> 00:33.658
seen Emily since the breakup,

00:33.659 --> 00:35.494
and I have been avoiding Langford's.

00:35.495 --> 00:36.798
I've also been taking the stairs

00:36.799 --> 00:38.061
instead of using the elevator,

00:38.062 --> 00:39.406
and donning a moustache and beret

00:39.407 --> 00:40.545
for trips through the lobby.

00:40.546 --> 00:42.434
That was you?

00:42.435 --> 00:45.670
Damn, I thought I had me
a Johnny Depp sighting.

00:45.671 --> 00:47.339
But I knew I was okay coming here today

00:47.340 --> 00:49.307
because it's her day off
and she just posted

00:49.308 --> 00:51.109
a picture of herself at the dog park,

00:51.110 --> 00:53.011
which must have been taken earlier

00:53.012 --> 00:56.114
because here you are and here are we.

00:56.115 --> 00:57.282
Hi, Felix.

00:57.283 --> 00:58.349
Good, and you?

01:00.952 --> 01:01.987
What?

01:01.988 --> 01:03.455
I was wondering when we were going

01:03.456 --> 01:05.123
to run into each other,
and now we have,

01:05.123 --> 01:06.458
and it feels right.

01:06.459 --> 01:07.692
The right stuff.

01:07.693 --> 01:10.562
We are astronauts of friendship.

01:10.563 --> 01:12.531
I wasn't sure how we would...

01:12.532 --> 01:14.099
You know, sin...

01:14.100 --> 01:15.563
I'm sorry, this is a little awkward.

01:15.564 --> 01:19.171
Awkward? No, it is goo... d.

01:19.172 --> 01:20.305
Good as gold.

01:20.306 --> 01:21.569
The gold medal of friendship...

01:21.570 --> 01:23.175
- goes to us.
- Oh!

01:23.176 --> 01:26.011
I don't know where to look.

01:26.012 --> 01:29.347
Okay, well, have to get back to work.

01:29.348 --> 01:30.515
You do that.

01:30.516 --> 01:31.849
Work it, girl!

01:33.685 --> 01:36.454
Well, that went better than I thought.

01:36.455 --> 01:39.357
Oh, God, look who's here.

01:39.358 --> 01:40.659
Uch, Rich Eisen.

01:40.660 --> 01:41.726
He always "swings by"

01:41.727 --> 01:43.628
after the ratings come out

01:43.629 --> 01:45.996
to tell me he beat me
and that he's my daddy.

01:48.200 --> 01:49.734
Madison.

01:49.735 --> 01:51.735
Eisen.

01:53.038 --> 01:55.540
Swing by to gloat about the ratings?

01:55.541 --> 01:57.842
Oh, what are ratings, anyway?

01:57.843 --> 02:01.745
Other than a highly accurate way
to determine who your daddy is?

02:04.182 --> 02:06.685
Was the astronaut of
friendship thing weird?

02:06.686 --> 02:08.720
No, no, it was good... it was playful.

02:08.721 --> 02:11.256
Say, Oscar, have you heard?

02:11.257 --> 02:13.158
The Broadcasters Charitable Trust

02:13.159 --> 02:15.560
has named me Humanitarian of the Year.

02:15.561 --> 02:18.029
They want someone to
introduce me at the banquet,

02:18.030 --> 02:19.598
and I thought of you.

02:19.599 --> 02:22.667
You really think I would do
that after you come down here

02:22.668 --> 02:24.636
and insult me in front of my friends?

02:24.637 --> 02:25.903
He'll be there.

02:26.905 --> 02:28.506
I'm sorry, Oscar, but, you know,

02:28.507 --> 02:30.242
you and Rich are on the same network,

02:30.243 --> 02:32.510
and the execs think it would
be "good corporate synergy."

02:32.511 --> 02:34.012
I just got the email.

02:34.013 --> 02:36.281
And with your ratings
being where they are,

02:36.282 --> 02:39.417
i.e., the crapper,

02:39.418 --> 02:43.321
it's probably not a good idea
to make the bigwigs mad.

02:43.322 --> 02:45.456
So we'll see you Friday.

02:46.691 --> 02:49.094
He could use a big wig.

02:49.095 --> 02:51.129
You could use a big wig!

02:51.130 --> 02:52.097
Ah, he's gone.

02:52.098 --> 02:53.164
Just like his hair.

02:53.165 --> 02:55.066
You've got no hair!

02:55.067 --> 02:56.067
Man, he always

02:56.068 --> 02:57.769
has to get the last word in.

02:57.770 --> 02:59.104
He's such a jerk.

02:59.105 --> 03:01.038
Reminds me of my bully
from high school.

03:02.140 --> 03:04.241
I wonder what she's doing now.

03:06.344 --> 03:07.712
I can't believe you got
to get up in public

03:07.713 --> 03:09.214
and give an award to that fool.

03:09.215 --> 03:10.749
Oh, don't worry, I'll buy a table

03:10.750 --> 03:12.884
and we'll all be there to
support you, right, guys?

03:12.885 --> 03:14.319
- Of course.
- Sounds fun.

03:14.320 --> 03:15.553
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- Oh, sorry.

03:15.554 --> 03:16.655
- I thought he was talking to me.
- He was asking you.

03:16.656 --> 03:17.689
- But you could go.
- I don't have to go.

03:17.690 --> 03:18.857
- I could go.
- I mean, I'm happy to.

03:18.858 --> 03:20.339
- Doesn't matter.
- Unless it's weird.

03:20.340 --> 03:21.523
- Up to you.
- It's your call.

03:21.524 --> 03:23.228
Oh, I hope there's a bar.

03:23.229 --> 03:25.163
It's okay, Felix, I don't have to go.

03:25.164 --> 03:27.932
No, no, of course we can both go.

03:27.933 --> 03:30.076
It doesn't have to be weird
if we don't want it to be.

03:30.077 --> 03:30.835
Are you sure?

03:30.836 --> 03:31.903
Of course!

03:31.904 --> 03:33.471
This can be the kickoff

03:33.472 --> 03:35.335
to the New Super-Cool
Laid-Back Friendship part

03:35.336 --> 03:36.308
of our relationship.

03:36.309 --> 03:37.309
(both laugh)

03:37.310 --> 03:39.443
- Uh, um...
- Oh, oh...

03:43.381 --> 03:45.116
Yeah, there's a bar.

03:45.117 --> 03:47.319
- Fantastic.
- Oh, thank God.

03:47.320 --> 03:50.689
