03:50.855 --> 03:52.424
OSCAR: <i>Even though I hate</i>

03:52.425 --> 03:54.192
having to say nice things
about that clown,

03:54.193 --> 03:55.660
the speech reads great.

03:55.661 --> 03:56.884
I just got a couple of tweaks.

03:56.885 --> 03:57.862
Hit me.

03:57.863 --> 03:59.798
You see here, when we say,

03:59.799 --> 04:03.301
"Rich Eisen is a good man
who does good things"?

04:03.302 --> 04:04.769
Uh-huh.

04:04.770 --> 04:07.871
Could we lose both of the "goods"?

04:09.941 --> 04:14.878
You want it to read, "Rich Eisen
is a man who has done things"?

04:15.947 --> 04:18.440
Yeah, that's better.

04:20.218 --> 04:22.252
Two questions: What time is
the banquet tomorrow,

04:22.253 --> 04:23.154
and was it just me,

04:23.155 --> 04:25.366
or did you get the sense
that Emily wants me back?

04:26.691 --> 04:29.127
7:30, and say what now?

04:29.128 --> 04:31.363
It just feel like Emily was
sending me signals.

04:31.364 --> 04:34.232
Oh, Felix, I hate to break it to you,

04:34.233 --> 04:36.101
but I think you're in denial.

04:36.102 --> 04:38.503
No, I'm not.

04:38.504 --> 04:39.637
Oh, wait, am I?

04:39.638 --> 04:41.806
(gasps): I am!

04:41.807 --> 04:45.410
Denial, I'm in denial.

04:45.411 --> 04:46.643
Yes!

04:50.115 --> 04:51.515
He's a weird little man.

04:54.252 --> 04:57.088
Okay, I call Eisen "Rich"
throughout the speech.

04:57.089 --> 05:01.758
Are we 100% sure he doesn't
sometimes go by "Dick"?

05:03.561 --> 05:06.164
Oh, no, not the whiteboard.

05:06.165 --> 05:09.768
Last time, he tried to
teach me about Congress.

05:09.769 --> 05:11.736
Thank you, Dani,
for helping me understand

05:11.737 --> 05:13.171
my current emotional state

05:13.172 --> 05:15.540
and showing me a path to recovery.

05:15.541 --> 05:18.843
The five stages of grief
were first defined

05:18.844 --> 05:21.646
by noted psychiatrist
Dr. Elisabeth Kubler-Ross.

05:21.647 --> 05:24.081
That chimp lady?

05:26.050 --> 05:29.254
I am clearly grieving the death
of my relationship with Emily.

05:29.255 --> 05:31.225
But the fact that I can
make that statement

05:31.226 --> 05:34.022
- _
- shows that I am through the first stage.

05:34.023 --> 05:35.460
So long, denial!

05:35.461 --> 05:38.137
- _
- I am no longer in you.

05:38.138 --> 05:39.130
So all I have to do is

05:39.131 --> 05:41.674
get through the next four steps
before tomorrow night's banquet,

05:41.675 --> 05:43.908
and I will be completely over Emily.

05:45.003 --> 05:46.538
I don't think it works that way.

05:46.539 --> 05:50.041
Maybe for chimps.

05:50.042 --> 05:51.876
But you're a human man.

05:51.877 --> 05:54.112
Oscar, you saw how I was
after my divorce.

05:54.113 --> 05:55.513
I was devastated for months

05:55.514 --> 05:57.023
because I couldn't let go of my grief.

05:57.024 --> 05:57.949
I can't go through that again.

05:57.950 --> 05:59.613
I've got to fast-forward
through the pain.

05:59.614 --> 06:01.553
I get that, but tomorrow
is awfully quick.

06:01.554 --> 06:03.588
Oh, I can do it,
I can master my emotions,

06:03.589 --> 06:05.757
knock through the next
four stages in the next...

06:05.758 --> 06:07.959
26 hours and 13 minutes.

06:07.960 --> 06:11.495
Look out, stage two,
I am coming for you!

06:14.232 --> 06:16.300
Oh, no, not the whiteboard.

06:17.669 --> 06:19.070
Hey, Oscar, I slipped Eisen

06:19.071 --> 06:20.505
a copy of your speech last night.

06:20.506 --> 06:21.506
And?

06:21.507 --> 06:23.141
Ah, he hated it.

06:23.142 --> 06:25.310
What? All it was was ass-kissing!

06:25.311 --> 06:26.544
Well, that's the problem.

06:26.545 --> 06:27.985
He picked you because you're rivals.

06:27.986 --> 06:29.450
He wants it to be more like a roast.

06:29.451 --> 06:31.416
He wants me to roast him?

06:31.417 --> 06:35.653
Like the sun roasts his balding head?

06:35.654 --> 06:38.256
Yeah, and then he'll come back
at you with his own jabs.

06:38.257 --> 06:40.492
Ooh, like how Oscar has
a face made for radio?

06:40.493 --> 06:42.427
(laughing)

06:42.428 --> 06:44.496
Or how he smells like
the business end of a baby?

06:44.497 --> 06:46.397
(laughing)

06:46.398 --> 06:50.168
Or how he looks like he's
trick-or-treating as a hamper.

06:50.169 --> 06:52.836
I don't like how quickly
you're coming up with these.

06:57.408 --> 06:58.843
I'm so angry!

06:58.844 --> 07:00.612
I gave her a year of my life

07:00.613 --> 07:02.947
and she chewed me up and spit me out!

07:02.948 --> 07:05.450
Why won't the universe
let me find love?

07:05.451 --> 07:09.621
Why, why, why, why, why?

07:09.622 --> 07:10.955
This isn't working.

07:10.956 --> 07:12.499
We've been at it for nearly an hour.

07:12.500 --> 07:14.559
Eight minutes.

07:14.560 --> 07:15.727
And yet I'm still angry.

07:15.728 --> 07:17.262
I think I know why.

07:17.263 --> 07:19.030
I think it's because my body knows

07:19.031 --> 07:20.598
that this isn't a real fight.

07:20.599 --> 07:23.635
So I'm going to need you
to fight me back, okay?

07:23.636 --> 07:25.299
Just give me everything
you've got, ready?

07:25.300 --> 07:26.622
I'm not going to fight you, okay?

07:26.623 --> 07:28.327
You don't even know
how to defend yourself.

07:28.328 --> 07:29.007
(laughs)

07:29.008 --> 07:30.308
You might be surprised, huh?

07:30.309 --> 07:32.110
Come on, come on, fight me, what?

07:32.111 --> 07:33.978
Or are you chicken?
Hmm? Who's a chicken?

07:33.979 --> 07:37.081
I bet somebody wanted to be
a real boxer, right? Huh?

07:37.082 --> 07:38.883
Not just a boxing teacher.

07:38.884 --> 07:40.852
And you know what they say:
those who can't do...

07:40.853 --> 07:42.486
(yelps)

07:47.592 --> 07:50.827
(weakly): Anger... stage... complete.

